SUMMARY:Natchez | InLight Human Rights Documentary Film Festival
DESCRIPTION:The city of Natchez\, Mississippi is known for its historical
  tourism rooted in the antebellum South. This film by director Suzannah H
 erbert examines the intersections of memory and race\, showcased through 
 various people in the town who guide outsiders through the town's sites. 
 Her examination into performances of history produce thought provoking qu
 estions surrounding truth and stewardship of the past.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The city of Natchez\, Mississippi is kn
 own for its historical tourism rooted in the antebellum South. This film 
