SUMMARY:Writing Hawa | InLight Human Rights Documentary Film Festival
DESCRIPTION:Filmed over five years\, Afghan director Najiba Noori intimat
 ely documents her mother Hawa's late-blooming independence after a child 
 marriageŌĆölearning to read\, starting a textile business\, and shelterin
 g her runaway granddaughter Zahra from abuse. As three generations of Haz
 ara women pursue emancipation amid patriarchal traditions\, the Taliban's
  2021 resurgence shatters their dreams\, forcing exile and remote resista
 nce.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Filmed over five years\, Afghan directo
 r Najiba Noori intimately documents her mother Hawa's late-blooming indep
 endence after a child marriageŌĆölearning to read\, starting a textile bu
 siness\, and sheltering her runaway granddaughter Zahra from abuse. As th
 ree generations of Hazara women pursue emancipation amid patriarchal trad
 itions\, the Taliban's 2021 resurgence shatters their dreams\, forcing ex
 ile and remote resistance.</p>
