SUMMARY:Below the Clouds/Sotto le novole w/Q&A | In Light Human Rights Do
 cumentary Film Festival
DESCRIPTION:In Below the Clouds\, Gianfranco Rosi's monumental black-and-
 white documentary captures Naples' hidden\, unglamorous sideŌĆöfocusing o
 n everyday lives\, municipal routines\, and subterranean historical layer
 s shadowed by Vesuvius and the simmering Phlegraean Fields. Amid quakes a
 nd fumaroles\, archaeologists excavate ancient ruins\, firefighters calm 
 fears\, law enforcement hunts tomb robbers\, and localsŌĆöfrom worshipper
 s at Madonna dell'Arco to Japanese diggers at Villa AugusteaŌĆönavigate d
 aily life. Blending past and present\, the film evokes a volatile time ma
 chine of history\, anxiety\, and resilience. Winner of the Special Jury P
 rize at the Venice Film Festival. [115 min\; documentary\; Italian with E
 nglish subtitles]A Q&amp\;A with Ahmed Tahsin Shams (PhD student\, IU Med
 ia School) and Joan Hawkins (professor emerita\, IU Media School) will fo
 llow the screening.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  In <i>Below the Clouds</i>\, Gianfranco
  Rosi's monumental black-and-white documentary captures Naples' hidden\, 
 unglamorous sideŌĆöfocusing on everyday lives\, municipal routines\, and 
 subterranean historical layers shadowed by Vesuvius and the simmering Phl
 egraean Fields. Amid quakes and fumaroles\, archaeologists excavate ancie
 nt ruins\, firefighters calm fears\, law enforcement hunts tomb robbers\,
  and localsŌĆöfrom worshippers at Madonna dell'Arco to Japanese diggers a
 t Villa AugusteaŌĆönavigate daily life. Blending past and present\, the f
 ilm evokes a volatile time machine of history\, anxiety\, and resilience.
  Winner of the Special Jury Prize at the Venice Film Festival. [115 min\;
  documentary\; Italian with English subtitles]</p><p><i><strong>A Q&amp\;
 A with Ahmed Tahsin Shams (PhD student\, IU Media School) and Joan Hawkin
 s (professor emerita\, IU Media School) will follow the screening.</stron
 g></i></p>
