SUMMARY:How Deep Is Your Love w/filmmaker | In Light Human Rights Documen
 tary Film Festival
DESCRIPTION:In How Deep Is Your Love\, marine biologists venture into Ear
 th's last wildernessŌĆöthe deep seaŌĆöto study "alien-like" creatures and
  ancient ecosystems thriving in darkness. As they race to map undiscovere
 d species\, the film reveals the urgent threat of deep-sea mining\, poise
 d to devastate these fragile habitats. Blending awe-inspiring exploration
  with a call to action\, it questions humanity's commitment to preserving
  an unseen and mysterious world. [101 min\; documentary\; English]A Q&amp
 \;A will follow the screening with filmmaker Eleanor Mortimer\, Dr. Teres
 a Kovacs (Germanic Studies\; Theatre\, Drama and Contemporary Dance)\, Dr
 . R. Andr├®s Guzm├Īn (Spanish and Portuguese\; Cultural Studies Program)\
 , and Ahmed Tahsin Shams (Media School) will follow the screening.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  In <i>How Deep Is Your Love</i>\, marin
 e biologists venture into Earth's last wildernessŌĆöthe deep seaŌĆöto stu
 dy "alien-like" creatures and ancient ecosystems thriving in darkness. As
  they race to map undiscovered species\, the film reveals the urgent thre
 at of deep-sea mining\, poised to devastate these fragile habitats. Blend
 ing awe-inspiring exploration with a call to action\, it questions humani
 ty's commitment to preserving an unseen and mysterious world. [101 min\; 
 documentary\; English]</p><p><i><strong>A Q&amp\;A will follow the screen
 ing with filmmaker Eleanor Mortimer\, Dr. Teresa Kovacs (Germanic Studies
 \; Theatre\, Drama and Contemporary Dance)\, Dr. R. Andr├®s Guzm├Īn (Span
 ish and Portuguese\; Cultural Studies Program)\, and Ahmed Tahsin Shams (
 Media School) will follow the screening.</strong></i></p>
