LOCATION:MCCALLA
GEO:39.170841;-86.5275
SUMMARY:By Their Own Hands: The Black Filmmakers Hall of Fame exhibit
DESCRIPTION:By Their Own Hands includes one-of-a-kind items such as Sidne
 y Poitier's autographed shooting script for Let's Do It Again (1975)\, th
 e Nicholas Brothers' tap shoes\, and letters from icons like Maya Angelou
  and Oprah Winfrey\, among others. The centerpiece is a stunning wall of 
 42 BFHFI inductees' handprints\, a distinction comparable to receiving a 
 star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame! Select examples of inductees' handpri
 nts include Lena Horne\, Eartha Kitt\, Richard Pryor\, and Billy Dee Will
 iams.  Special thanks to University Collections at McCalla for collaborat
 ing with and helping install the exhibit\, and to the IU Foundation's Aff
 inity Giving Group ŌĆō Black Philanthropy Circle (BPC) for generously awa
 rding the BFCA a grant to frame the handprints in Summer 2024.By Their Ow
 n Hands will remain on display through Spring 2026\, and the BFCA will ho
 ld an educational event to re-engage the exhibit space during Black Histo
 ry Month. Contact us at bfca@iu.edu to request an appointment to view BFH
 FI collection items not curated for the exhibit.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><em data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">By
  Their Own Hands</em> includes one-of-a-kind items such as Sidney Poitier
 's autographed shooting script for <em>Let's Do It Again</em> (1975)\, th
 e Nicholas Brothers' tap shoes\, and letters from icons like Maya Angelou
  and Oprah Winfrey\, among others. The centerpiece is a stunning wall of 
 42 BFHFI inductees' handprints\, a distinction comparable to receiving a 
 star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame! Select examples of inductees' handpri
 nts include Lena Horne\, Eartha Kitt\, Richard Pryor\, and Billy Dee Will
 iams.</p><p>  Special thanks to University Collections at McCalla for col
 laborating with and helping install the exhibit\, and to the IU Foundatio
 n's Affinity Giving Group ŌĆō Black Philanthropy Circle (BPC) for generou
 sly awarding the BFCA a grant to frame the handprints in Summer 2024.</p>
 <p><em>By Their Own Hands</em> will remain on display through Spring 2026
 \, and the BFCA will hold an educational event to re-engage the exhibit s
 pace during Black History Month. Contact us at bfca@iu.edu to request an 
 appointment to view BFHFI collection items not curated for the exhibit.</
 p>
